definition.value: The parent compound of the beta-carbolines, a tricyclic structure comprising an indole ring system ortho- fused to C-3 and C-4 of a pyridine ring.
A triacyl-sn-glycerol in which the which the acyl groups at position 1 is specified as hexadecanoyl, while those at positions 2 and 3 are specified as octadecanoyl
